\v 22 Their father¦190947 Efrayim¦190946 mourned¦190945 for \add ≈quite some time\add*, and¦190950 his relatives¦190951 came¦190950 to comfort¦190952 him¦190952.
\v 23 Then¦190954 he \add ≈slept with\add* his wife and she \add ≈got pregnant¦190958\add* and \add ≈gave¦190959 birth¦190959 to\add* a son. \add @Efrayim\add* \add ≈named him\add* Beriah¦190965 \add (which sounds like the Hebrew word for ‘trouble’)\add*, because \add ≈of the recent tragedy in their family\add*.
