\c 9
\s1 Those who returned from captivity
\rem /s1 The restored community; The People Who Returned from Captivity
\p
\v 1 \add ≈So\add* all Yisrael \add ≈were listed in genealogy\add*, and yes, they're written¦191556 on the scroll¦191559 of Yisrael's kings¦191560.
\rem /s1 The Returning Exiles; The People in Jerusalem
\p Then Yehudah \add (Judah)\add* was taken¦191563 into exile¦191563 to Babylon¦191564 because of their¦191565 unfaithfulness¦191565.
\v 2 The first¦191569 \add ≈to return and resettle their land and\add* their cities were \add some\add* priests¦191574, Levites¦191575, temple¦191576 servants¦191576, and \add other\add* Israelis.\x + \xo 9:2-3: \xt Ezr 2:27; Neh 7:73.\x*
