\p
\v 19 Shallum was Kore's¦191836 son, Kore was Evyasaph's son, and Evyasaph was Korah's son. Shallum and his relatives¦191843 from his clan (Korah's descendants), had the duty of being gatekeepers, responsible to guard the entrances¦191860 to Yahweh's temple as their¦191854 ancestors¦191854 had done.
\v 20 \add ≈Previously\add* Pinehas (Eleazar's¦191865 son) \add ≈had supervised\add* the gatekeepers. Yahweh¦191870 was with \add @Pinehas\add*.
\p
\v 21 Zekaryah (Meshelemyah's¦191876 son) was gatekeeper¦191877 of the entrance¦191878 to the assembly tent.
\v 22 \add ≈Altogether, there were 212 men chosen¦191883 to guard the gates\add*. \add ≈The records of the clans in their villages¦191890 listed their names\add*. \add King\add* David¦191894 and \add ≈the prophet\add* Shemuel \add (Samuel¦191895)\add* \add ≈appointed¦191893 them because they¦191889 were dependable\add*.
