\v 24 There were gatekeepers¦191915 on each of the \add temple's\add* four¦191912 sides¦191913: east, west, north¦191918, and¦191919 south¦191919.
\v 25 Their relatives¦191921 in their villages¦191922 would come in from time to time \add to relieve them\add* for seven¦191924 days¦191925
\v 26 because the four¦191937 leaders of the gatekeepers¦191939 were Levites¦191941, and they were \add also\add* \add ≈trusted¦191935 to supervise\add* the chambers¦191945 and the treasuries¦191947 in God's¦191949 residence.
